Bill Cosby has caused me to reflect on my own life and answer the question: who am I in public, and who am I in private? I am thankful the answer has been largely the same. But yet I am starkly reminded, that if I am not careful about what I allow my mind and heart to meditate on, I am just a few steps away from where Mr. Cosby has been. I have been influenced by the lie of pornography for many years as a youth, objectifying and degrading women in a sexual manner and contributing to a dark, violent industry, the impact of which is many social ills. I have been saddened by the response of many watching Bill Cosby's life, vehemently judging him, ostracizing him, condemning him, and even calling to end his life. While I do not condone any of his behavior, he is still a person at the end of the day who is a person that is still in need of healing, grace, and kindness to change.
